title: Mannequin - Official Cinematic Reveal Trailer
description: Mannequin is an asymmetric VR multiplayer game developed by Fast Travel Games. Aliens have arrived on Earth with the ability to freeze humans in time with a single touch. Special Agents have been deployed to neutralize the threat once and for all. Play as alien Mannequins and set up deadly ambushes by posing as humans frozen in time or as human Agents and wield high-tech gadgets to neutralize the Mannequins from a distance in 5-player matches. Mannequin is launching in 2024 for PlayStation VR2, Meta Quest, and SteamVR.

title: Apple's Latest Reveals at the iPhone 15 Wonderlust Event
description:
Join us as we unpack the latest highlights from Apple's iPhone 15 Wonderlust Event! First on the stage is the Apple Watch Series 9, boasting the S9 chip for all-day battery life and an intuitive 'Double Tap' gesture, complemented by a stylish new watch face.
But the real game-changer is the iPhone 15, marking a significant shift with its USB-C port and inheriting the dynamic island feature from the iPhone 14. Gamers, get ready for the iPhone 15 Pro, packed with hardware-accelerated ray tracing and ports of great console games like Resident Evil: Village and Assassin's Creed Mirage. It also introduces an action button for quick customization and flaunts a sleek titanium frame for durability and design. Don't miss the full video for all the details on the latest Apple products.

#IGN

title: Mortal Kombat 1 - Full Movie (All Cutscenes in 4K)
description:
Wondering where the story goes after Liu Kang rebooted the timeline in MK11? Check out the full movie of Mortal Kombat 1, including all cutscenes in 4K! This is the full story mode, so here’s your spoiler warning!

Scorpion, Sub Zero, Raiden, Mileena, Shang Tsung, and others return in MK1, and the story is a soft reboot of the entire Mortal Kombat story. Having defeated Kronika, Fire God Liu Kang sets a new narrative in motion, and old nemeses such as Shao Kahn (now General Shao), Quan Chi, and Nitara return! Other single-player modes include Arcade Towers, Invasions Mode, and more– but for now, we hope you enjoy the MK1 Story Mode.

title: Worms: The Board Game - Official Gameplay Trailer
description: Check out the gameplay trailer for Worms: The Board Game. Worms: The Board Game will see the iconic invertebrates star in their debut tabletop game. Get ready to deploy your miniatures from the classic strategy game, featuring hilarious poses and iconic weaponry. A Kickstarter campaign is available now.

Nintendo Direct Watch Party Livestream (9.14.2023)
description: Join us as we watch the Septemeber Nintendo Direct live in a watch party. We'll have live reactions to all the upcoming news about games coming this Winter to Nintendo Switch and any surprises they might sneak in.

title: Mortal Kombat 1 - Every Starter Fatality In 4K
description:
Mortal Kombat 1 has a TON of stuff to unlock at first, including characters and even finishing moves like fatalities and brutalities! While we're busy unlocking all the other stuff, here are all the starter fatalities for every character, including Havik and Jean Claude Van Damme Johnny Cage in 4K, 60 FPS.

Unique to Mortal Kombat 1 is the Kameo system; Kameos are assist characters you can tag in to help your main player character. Mainstays like Sonya, Kano, Scorpion, Sub Zero, and Jax all have their own separate movelists you can activate to help start your offense, break an enemy's combo, or even help with neutral. There are even Kameo fatalities, which we've made sure to show off here!

title: Mortal Kombat 1 - All Fatal Blows (Starting Characters)
description:
Mortal Kombat 1 has a TON of stuff to unlock in-game, including characters and fatalities. Here's all the fatal blows (formerly called X-Ray attacks) for the characters that are initially available on the starting roster, before you start unlocking things. We'll be back soon with updated compilations of all the characters, so make sure you check back in a few! And we're in 4K, 60 FPS, baby.

Unique to Mortal Kombat 1 is the Kameo system; Kameos are assist characters you can tag in to help your main player character. Mainstays like Sonya, Kano, Scorpion, Sub Zero, and Jax all have their own separate movelists you can activate to help start your offense, break an enemy's combo, or even help with neutral. There are even Kameo fatalities! Each Fatal Blow has two parts: your main character, and your kameo. Since there are more player characters than kameos in the initial roster, there's a bit of overlap in this video and you'll see some more than once.

title: How Do You Review a Soulslike on a Tight Deadline? - Beyond Clip
description:
Travis Northup reviews tons of games for IGN, most recently Lies of P. We had him on Beyond this week to chat about what's different when playing through games on a tight deadline without any guides or walkthroughs - specifically, what it's like tacking the historically tough-as-nails and frequently obtuse soulslike genre.

Ahsoka stars Rosario Dawson, Natasha Liu Bordizzo, Wes Chatham, Mary Elizabeth Winstead, Lars Mikkelsen, Ray Stevenson, Eman Esfandi, Diana Lee Inosanto, Hayden Christensen and more. The Creator - Official Final Trailer (2023) John David Washington, Gemma Chan, Ken Watanabe
description:
Check out the final trailer for The Creator, an upcoming sci-fi action thriller movie starring John David Washington, Gemma Chan, Ken Watanabe, Sturgill Simpson, Madeleine Yuna Voyles, and Allison Janney.

The Creator is set amidst a future war between the human race and the forces of artificial intelligence. Joshua (Washington), a hardened ex-special forces agent grieving the disappearance of his wife (Chan), is recruited to hunt down and kill the Creator, the elusive architect of advanced AI who has developed a mysterious weapon with the power to end the war…and mankind itself. Joshua and his team of elite operatives journey across enemy lines, into the dark heart of AI-occupied territory, only to discover the world-ending weapon he’s been instructed to destroy is an AI in the form of a young child (Voyles). 

The Creator is directed by Gareth Edwards, with a screenplay by Gareth Edwards and Chris Weitz from a story by Gareth Edwards. The producers are Gareth Edwards, p.g.a., Kiri

#IGN #Gaming #CrashBandicoot

title: iPhone 15 Pro - Official A17 Pro & Mobile Gaming Trailer
description:
The iPhone 15 Pro arrives soon -- and its coming with much more than that coveted USB-C port. With Apple's new A17 Pro performance chip, game developers have experimented and implemented ways to enhance the mobile gaming experience. Explore heavily detailed environments like never before while enjoying faster response times on favorites like Genshin Impact. 

In a massive leap forward for mobile gaming, A17 Pro is powerul enough to run games previously only available via PC or consoles on the iPhone 15 Pro. What does that mean? It means Resident Evil Village, Resident Evil 4, Assassin's Creed Mirage and more in your pocket by early 2024. During their presentation of the new featured introduced with the iPhone 15 Pro, Apple touts the A17 Pro performance chip as the future of mobile gaming. If one thing is certain, it's that mobile gamers have quite the year to look forward to. 

The iPhone 15 Pro is available for pre-order starting September 15th and launches on September 22nd.

#IGN

title: Lies of P: 12 Ways It’s Different From Bloodborne
description:
Our noses might start growing if we said Lies of P didn't look, sound, and play A LOT like Bloodborne - which is definitely not a bad thing - but it does make a few very subtle changes to FromSoftware's established formula that shake things up quite a bit. We break down some of the big (and little) differences between the two, and go off on a few tangents because we're very excited about this game.

#IGN #Gaming #LiesOfP

title: Lies of P Review
description:
Lies of P reviewed by Travis Northup on Xbox Series X, also available on Xbox One, PlayStation, and PC.

This retelling of Pinocchio may not branch out very far from its soulslike inspiration, but like a marionette controlled by a skilled puppet master, it plays the part extremely well in a wonderfully dark fantasy world.  If you’ve been waiting for a Bloodborne remaster or sequel that may never come, Lies of P is the next best thing.

title: Timberborn - Official 2nd Anniversary Trailer
description: Timberborn, the beaver-tastic real-time strategy game from Mechanistry, is celebrating its second anniversary with this new trailer that celebrates 1 million copies sold by showcasing beaver hot tubs, new vertical architecture, new water physics, new environmental challenges like droughts, robo-beavers, two beaver factions, and more. Timberborn is available now on PC (via Steam, Epic Games Store, and GOG).

title: The Marvels - Official IMAX Teaser Trailer (2023) Brie Larson, Teyonah Parris, Iman Vellani
description:
Check out the IMAX teaser trailer for The Marvels for another look at the upcoming movie. The Marvels stars Brie Larson, Teyonah Parris, Iman Vellani, Zawe Ashton, Gary Lewis, Seo-Jun Park, Zenobia Shroff, Mohan Kapur, Saagar Shaikh, and Samuel L. Jackson.

In Marvel Studios’ The Marvels, Carol Danvers aka Captain Marvel has reclaimed her identity from the tyrannical Kree and taken revenge on the Supreme Intelligence. But unintended consequences see Carol shouldering the burden of a destabilized universe. When her duties send her to an anomalous wormhole linked to a Kree revolutionary, her powers become entangled with that of Jersey City super-fan Kamala Khan, aka Ms. Marvel, and Carol’s estranged niece, now S.A.B.E.R. astronaut Captain Monica Rambeau. Together, this unlikely trio must team up and learn to work in concert to save the universe as “The Marvels.”

title: NBA 2K24 Video Review
description:
NBA 2K24 reviewed on Xbox Series X by Ben Vollmer. Also available on PlayStation 5. Narrated by Ryan McCaffrey. (Note: the PS4/Xbox One/PC versions are based on the previous-generation version and are not covered by this review.)

"The old adage “a tale of two halves” really encapsulates the NBA 2K24 experience. On one hand, the hardcourt experience is as good as it ever has been (as we should demand from a game that iterates annually), and there are a handful of game modes that allow all of that to be enjoyed without interruption. On the other, much more nefarious hand, MyCareer is nearly unplayable unless you open your wallet or endure an absurd grind. Even worse, mechanics like badge regression reinforce the worst parts of the microtransaction scheme. Beneath those issues, NBA 2K24 still offers a solid basketball experience, but it requires looking in the right places. Star Wars: Jedi Survivor PS5 vs Xbox Series X|S Patch 7 Performance Review
description:
Jedi Survivor was another hit for Respawn earlier this year, but the performance mode and resolution was not so highly regarded. With Patch 7 dropping last week the team have produced a Jedi like return for console & PC. Improved FX, resolution and a closer lock on 60FPS. Along with DLSS added to PC and engine improvements, is this a new hope for all players?
